body.description: BISSELL® CleanView® Swivel Rewind Pet Reach vacuum provides the ultimate cleaning experience for pet parents. It’s designed with powerful suction and packed with convenient features, like a multi-surface TRIPLE ACTION™ Brush Roll with Scatter-Free Technology, so you can pick up messes with less debris scatter. It also has a lightweight design and swivel steering, so you can easily maneuver throughout your home while cleaning. But CleanView® Swivel Rewind Pet Reach vacuum isn’t limited to floors — its Quick Release Extension Wand is always on and always ready to clean, so you can easily and quickly get to any above-floor or hard-to-reach places your pet may leave behind a mess. And when the cleaning is done, all it takes is a press of a button to rewind the cord and store away. CleanView® Swivel Rewind Pet Reach vacuum doesn’t just clean up after pets — it helps save them, too! BISSELL proudly supports BISSELL Pet Foundation® and its mission to help save homeless pets. When you buy a BISSELL® product, you help save pets. We’re proud to design products that help make pet messes, odors and pet homelessness disappear.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great vacuum! Exceeded my expectations!
reviews.reviewText: I'm VERY picky about vacuum cleaners.I love everything about this vacuum!Everything is easy to use; the dust cup is easy to remove, works well on bare floors and carpet, the retractable cord works great! The attachments are easily accessible.I can't think of anything I would change.Kudos to Bissell for a great product!I appreciate the donation to animal rescue!This is my first Bissell product. It will not be my last!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Love this vacuum! Has a great wand for cleaning ceiling or around baseboards. Easy to clean and put back together. Has nice maneuverability with the swivel head. It isn't heavy has about the same weight as others. The noise of the vacuum was less than our last one. The suction was just amazing when we used it for the first time, it had picked up so much more than our last vacuum ever had. Has nice handle to maneuver it around. It doesn't have a headlamp but then again, we don't vacuum in the dark, not really necessary. The extra tools that come with it hangs on the vacuum which is really convenient. I do like how the hose connects and easy to replace if ever needed. Well made and we would buy again and again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worth every penny
reviews.reviewText: This vacume does everything promised. Excellent at picking up pet hair! Light weight, easy to maneuver, easy clean canister, love being able to push a button and have the cord rewind!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I can't believe I've gone this long without this vac!
reviews.reviewText: For starters, once I received this vac this morning I had to try it right away. Was literally a snap to put together. It picked up everything & then some. When I went to empty it out I read the manual & saw that you can remove the inside plastic filter/tube, by turning it clockwise. It came out & went back in just as easy, and I was able to remove any pet hair that was in the upper portion of the tank. I haven't tried the attachments yet, but I really like the extended reach should I ever need to use it. The base swivels to get into those hard to reach places. After spending a small fortune on a Dyson that died after a few year, I said never again would I pay that much for a vac. Not only was this affordable, but it's a DYNAMO! My carpet hasn't looked this good in awhile (it's extremely old & needs to be replaced). Best of all it gives back to help animals who really need it, so I wasn't at all hesitant about purchasing it. While some people griped about it not having a frontal light, you really don't need it when it picks up absolutely everything in it's path. It is a bit on the loud side, but no more than any other upright, high suction vacuum. This is great for older people with arthritic hands as well, bc everything snaps in & out of place easily. It was a bit on the heavier side though, but I probably just had the floor setting too low (I just wanted the carpet cleaned, and didn't really care about anything else, was in a rush lol O.C.D. on my part). Overall I would definitely buy it again. Great buy

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works so great
reviews.reviewText: We’ve been using cordless vacuums for the last 7 years and threw many away. This vacuum is incredible. We have three boys 5 and under and this cleans up every mess trailed throughout the house. My favorite part is the button that retracts the cord. Easy to maneuver and sucks up everything in one swoop.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Holy Crap! I love this thing.
reviews.reviewText: I have used a Dyson for several years and it was great in its prime but had lost its effectiveness. With two resident dogs and occasional foster dogs plus daughters with long hair, well, it’s been an epic hair battle for years.What I love: Hair doesn’t stick on the roller. Picks up anything on the floor, baseboards or ceiling for cobwebs spectacularly. Canister of hair, dander and dirt empties easily. Like the way the attachments go on. My old Dyson was a puzzle to get the attachments to stay - well- attached. Love the cord rewind so that’s neatly tucked away. Lightweight but powerful. Easy to move aroundWhat I wish was different: could use a little longer cord. It’s generous but another 6-12 inches would be great.If you have pets or kids or just dirty floors, buy this vacuum!

reviews.reviewText: Very powerful. It picks up everything. The build quality is good but it seems a bit over-engineered and delicate. I would be careful when pulling or returning the cord in the cord mechanism.
